Japanese band Kroi's latest music video for the "Method" single was recorded using 40 <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-16-pro/">iPhone 16 Pro</a> models, according to Apple.<br/>
<br/>
<div class="center-wrap"><iframe title="Kroi - Method [Official Video] #SAKAMOTODAYS" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/oioOfrRKhrI" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div><br/>
The iPhones were used to capture video from every angle simultaneously, with all of the shots merged into a single 3-minute music video.<br/>
<br/>
Apple <a href="https://www.instagram.com/reel/DMq7uo7yS_S/">shared details</a> on Instagram, and Apple's marketing chief Greg Joswiak also highlighted the video on social media.<br/>
<br/>
